\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Internet of Things (IoT) has exponentially increased the number of connected devices, from home appliances to industrial equipment. However, this connectivity presents significant cybersecurity challenges. Devices often lack robust security features, making them vulnerable to attacks. Common threats include data breaches, denial of service attacks, and malware infections. To address these issues, IT professionals focus on securing device connectivity and data integrity through advanced encryption methods, regular software updates, and network security solutions. The ongoing development of security standards and protocols is crucial to safeguarding the expanding IoT landscape.\
